org.fluidity.composition.container.spi

Interface ContextNode


  • public interface ContextNode
    A node in a dependency graph where qualifier annotations may be accepted and/or provided. An object implementing this interface is created for every component class in a container and these objects help in the management of component context when resolving dependencies.

    Usage

    You don't interact with an internal interface.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Class<?> contextConsumer()
      Returns the class that may accept qualifier annotations at this node.
      Annotation[] providedContext()
      Returns the list of annotations defined at this node that may comprise the context of some other component.
